# Brain Manager

## Before Any Task

| Check | Where |
|-------|-------|
| Is the component already built? | `.cursor/memory/components-map.md` |
| Is the API endpoint already mapped? | `.cursor/memory/api-map.md` |
| Is the phase already complete? | `.cursor/memory/completed-tasks.md` |
| What's the current active work? | `.cursor/memory/current-focus.md` |

## Scanning Rules

- Never re-read files already in your context in the same session
- Don't scan `node_modules/`, `artifacts/`, `.next/`, `dist/`
- When a user says "sync frontend/backend" → check `api-map.md` for gaps first
- When a user says "phase FN/BN" → read `pending-tasks.md` for exact scope

## Task Scope

- Max **1 module** touched per task unless explicitly spanning modules
- Fix only the root cause — never refactor unrelated code
- If a file exists and works → leave it alone

## After Completing Work

Update these memory files:
- `completed-tasks.md` → mark the task done
- `current-focus.md` → update last edited files and next action
- `components-map.md` → add any new components created
- `api-map.md` → add any new API hooks created
